5 (f) In conducting the study required by this section, the
6 commission may consult with or invite comments from:
7 (1) electric utilities;
8 (2) the office of utility consumer counselor;
9 (3) associations or organizations representing utility
10 ratepayers;
11 (4) regional transmission organizations;
12 (5) state and local economic development agencies or
13 organizations; and
14 (6) other stakeholders.
15 The commission may incorporate any information or comments
16 received under this subsection in its report under subsection (g).
17 (g) The commission shall include in the annual report that the
18 commission is required to submit under IC 8-1-1-14 before
